Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
Laboratory results are largely within normal limits. Mild anemia is present (hemoglobin slightly below normal), and chloride is mildly elevated; these findings may warrant clinical correlation but are not acutely alarming. Glucose control (HbA1c) is at the upper end of normal. Renal function, electrolytes, and blood counts are otherwise unremarkable. No urgent laboratory concerns identified.
